“psychiatrist”  means  a  registered  medical  practitioner  with 
qualifications, training and experience in the discipline of psychiatry 
recognized by the Director General;

“psychiatric hospital” means a government psychiatric hospital or a 
private  psychiatric  hospital  including  a  gazetted  private  psychiatric 
hospital;

“private  psychiatric  hospital”  means  any  premises  licensed  as  a 
private  psychiatric  hospital  under  the  Private  Healthcare  Facilities 
and Services Act 1998 [Act 586];

“Court”  means  the  High  Court,  a  Sessions  Court  or  a  Magistrate 
Court or a Syariah Court as the context may require, and includes a 
Judge whether sitting in Court or in Chambers;

“social  welfare  officer”  means  any  social  welfare  officer  in  the 
Ministry  of  Health,  Malaysia  or  in  the  Ministry  or  Department 
responsible for welfare services;

“registered medical practitioner” means a person who is registered 
as such under the Medical Act 1971 [Act 50] and who holds a valid 
practicing certificate under the Act;

“community mental health centre” means a government community 
mental  health  centre  or  a  private  community  mental  health  centre, 
and includes a gazetted private community mental health centre;

“government community mental health centre” means any premises 
appointed to be a government community mental health centre under 
section 33;

“private  community  mental  health  centre”  means  any  premises 
licensed  as  a  private  community  mental  health  centre  under  the 
Private Healthcare Facilities and Services Act 1998;

“psychiatric  nursing  home”  means  a  government  psychiatric 
nursing  home  or  a  private  psychiatric  nursing  home,  and  includes  a 
gazetted private psychiatric nursing home;

“government  psychiatric  nursing  home”  means  any  premises 
appointed to be a government psychiatric nursing home under section 
27;

“private psychiatric nursing home” means any premises licensed as 
a  private  psychiatric  nursing  home  under  the  Private  Healthcare 
Facilities and Services Act 1998;

(a) the  payment  of  his  debts,  including  any  debt  or 
expenditure  incurred    for    his  maintenance  or  for  his 
benefit;

(b) by  his  guardian  in  the  case  of  a  minor  or  a  relative  in 
the case of an adult, if the patient is incapable of giving 
consent;

(i)  to  prescribe  all  matters  relating  to  the  issue  of 
communication  by  and  with  persons  detained  in 
psychiatric hospitals;

(l)  to provide for acceptable quality assurance and quality 
control  in  respect  of  psychiatric  hospitals,  psychiatric 
nursing homes and community mental health centres;

(b)  insert  after  the  words  “directions  as 
the”  the  words  “Medical  Director  or”; 
